ngs about Catholicism, but this is not the anti-Catholicism of the past.\", \"from\": 798, \"to\": 932, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"no doubt\", \"from\": 807, \"to\": 815}, {\"ngram\": \"many liberal elites\", \"from\": 821, \"to\": 840}, {\"ngram\": \"negative feelings\", \"from\": 846, \"to\": 863}, {\"ngram\": \"Catholicism\", \"from\": 870, \"to\": 881}, {\"ngram\": \"Catholicism\", \"from\": 908, \"to\": 919}, {\"ngram\": \"the past\", \"from\": 923, \"to\": 931}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the bad old days, Catholic immigrants from Europe were seen as a threat to the purity of the white Anglo-Saxon Protestant (WASP) establishment and its power in America.\", \"from\": 934, \"to\": 1105, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 955, \"end\": 963, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 0.9998984658654222, \"rank\": 0.00010151909565381063, \"text\": \"Catholic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}, {\"begin\": 1060, \"end\": 1064, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/White_Anglo-Saxon_Protestants\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.910467615542683e-35, \"text\": \"WASP\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/White_Anglo-Saxon_Protestants\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/White_Anglo-Saxon_Protestants\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the bad old days\", \"from\": 937, \"to\": 953}, {\"ngram\": \"Europe\", \"from\": 980, \"to\": 986}, {\"ngram\": \"a threat\", \"from\": 1000, \"to\": 1008}, {\"ngram\": \"the purity\", \"from\": 1012, \"to\": 1022}, {\"ngram\": \"its power\", \"from\": 1084, \"to\": 1093}, {\"ngram\": \"America\", \"from\": 1097, \"to\": 1104}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They were treated like today's immigrants from Africa, Asia and Latin America, segregated into poor neighborhoods and forced to work long hours to support their families.\", \"from\": 1106, \"to\": 1276, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"today's immigrants\", \"from\": 1129, \"to\": 1147}, {\"ngram\": \"Africa\", \"from\": 1153, \"to\": 1159}, {\"ngram\": \"Asia\", \"from\": 1161, \"to\": 1165}, {\"ngram\": \"Latin America\", \"from\": 1170, \"to\": 1183}, {\"ngram\": \"poor neighborhoods\", \"from\": 1201, \"to\": 1219}, {\"ngram\": \"long hours\", \"from\": 1239, \"to\": 1249}, {\"ngram\": \"their families\", \"from\": 1261, \"to\": 1275}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sadly, many white Catholics treat these newcomers like their grandparents were treated in the past.\", \"from\": 1278, \"to\": 1377, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1296, \"end\": 1305, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 0.9996008760898378, \"rank\": 0.0003992231591542304, \"text\": \"Catholics\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"these newcomers\", \"from\": 1312, \"to\": 1327}, {\"ngram\": \"their grandparents\", \"from\": 1333, \"to\": 1351}, {\"ngram\": \"the past\", \"from\": 1368, \"to\": 1376}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They join in opposing Mexican immigrants who are predominantly Catholic.\", \"from\": 1378, \"to\": 1450, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1400, \"end\": 1407, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mexican_Americans\", \"score\": 0.7004683250455934, \"rank\": 0.33170013713557134, \"text\": \"Mexican\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mexican_Americans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mexican_Americans\"}], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Some even join the KKK, which historically went after Blacks, Jews and Catholics.\", \"from\": 1451, \"to\": 1532, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1470, \"end\": 1473, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ku_Klux_Klan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.457050269354092e-33, \"text\": \"KKK\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ku_Klux_Klan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ku_Klux_Klan\"}, {\"begin\": 1513, \"end\": 1517, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jews\", \"score\": 0.9994445227023461, \"rank\": 0.000555786024209706, \"text\": \"Jews\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jews\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jews\"}, {\"begin\": 1522, \"end\": 1531, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 0.9996008760898378, \"rank\": 0.0003992231591542304, \"text\": \"Catholics\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Blacks\", \"from\": 1505, \"to\": 1511}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Today's attacks on Catholicism are different.\", \"from\": 1534, \"to\": 1579, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Today's attacks\", \"from\": 1534, \"to\": 1549}, {\"ngram\": \"Catholicism\", \"from\": 1553, \"to\": 1564}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They are more anticlerical than anti-Catholic.\", \"from\": 1580, \"to\": 1626, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Much of the antagonism is aimed at policies adopted by the Catholic hierarchy.\", \"from\": 1628, \"to\": 1706, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1687, \"end\": 1695, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 0.9998984658654222, \"rank\": 0.00010151909565381063, \"text\": \"Catholic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the antagonism\", \"from\": 1636, \"to\": 1650}, {\"ngram\": \"policies\", \"from\": 1663, \"to\": 1671}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The bishops have a perfect right to take positions on public policy, but do not be surprised that it results in name calling.\", \"from\": 1707, \"to\": 1832, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The bishops\", \"from\": 1707, \"to\": 1718}, {\"ngram\": \"a perfect right\", \"from\": 1724, \"to\": 1739}, {\"ngram\": \"positions\", \"from\": 1748, \"to\": 1757}, {\"ngram\": \"public policy\", \"from\": 1761, \"to\": 1774}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It is not surprising, for example, that gays were mad when bishops labeled them as \\\"intrinsically disordered,\\\" spent millions of dollars opposing gay marriage and said they should not be allowed to adopt children.\", \"from\": 1834, \"to\": 2047, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"example\", \"from\": 1860, \"to\": 1867}, {\"ngram\": \"gays\", \"from\": 1874, \"to\": 1878}, {\"ngram\": \"bishops\", \"from\": 1893, \"to\": 1900}, {\"ngram\": \"millions\", \"from\": 1951, \"to\": 1959}, {\"ngram\": \"dollars\", \"from\": 1963, \"to\": 1970}, {\"ngram\": \"gay marriage\", \"from\": 1980, \"to\": 1992}, {\"ngram\": \"children\", \"from\": 2038, \"to\": 2046}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Likewise, feminists have seen the bishops oppose them on birth control, abortion rights and the Equal Rights Amendment (ERA).\", \"from\": 2049, \"to\": 2174, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"feminists\", \"from\": 2059, \"to\": 2068}, {\"ngram\": \"the bishops\", \"from\": 2079, \"to\": 2090}, {\"ngram\": \"birth control\", \"from\": 2106, \"to\": 2119}, {\"ngram\": \"abortion rights\", \"from\": 2121, \"to\": 2136}, {\"ngram\": \"the Equal Rights Amendment\", \"from\": 2141, \"to\": 2167}, {\"ngram\": \"ERA\", \"from\": 2169, \"to\": 2172}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Democrats are also angry at the bishops who want to ban prochoice politicians from Communion.\", \"from\": 2175, \"to\": 2268, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2175, \"end\": 2184, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Democrats\", \"score\": 0.9998868179645783, \"rank\": 0.00010994345559046089, \"text\": \"Democrats\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Democrats\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Democrats\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the bishops\", \"from\": 2203, \"to\": 2214}, {\"ngram\": \"prochoice politicians\", \"from\": 2231, \"to\": 2252}, {\"ngram\": \"Communion\", \"from\": 2258, \"to\": 2267}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Add to this the general antagonism aimed at the church because of the failure of the bishops to deal with abusive priests.\", \"from\": 2270, \"to\": 2392, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the general antagonism\", \"from\": 2282, \"to\": 2304}, {\"ngram\": \"the church\", \"from\": 2314, \"to\": 2324}, {\"ngram\": \"the failure\", \"from\": 2336, \"to\": 2347}, {\"ngram\": \"the bishops\", \"from\": 2351, \"to\": 2362}, {\"ngram\": \"abusive priests\", \"from\": 2376, \"to\": 2391}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It is regrettable but not surprising when the rhetoric of these groups sometimes sounds anti-Catholic rather than simply anticlerical.\", \"from\": 2394, \"to\": 2528, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the rhetoric\", \"from\": 2436, \"to\": 2448}, {\"ngram\": \"these groups\", \"from\": 2452, \"to\": 2464}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A few have even crossed the line by defacing or destroying church property, which is unacceptable and criminal.\", \"from\": 2529, \"to\": 2640, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the line\", \"from\": 2553, \"to\": 2561}, {\"ngram\": \"church property\", \"from\": 2588, \"to\": 2603}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But Catholics need to keep this in perspective.\", \"from\": 2642, \"to\": 2689, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2646, \"end\": 2655, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 0.9996008760898378, \"rank\": 0.0003992231591542304, \"text\": \"Catholics\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"perspective\", \"from\": 2677, \"to\": 2688}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We are not under the same systemic threat of hate crimes as are Jews and Blacks.\", \"from\": 2690, \"to\": 2770, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2754, \"end\": 2758, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jews\", \"score\": 0.9994445227023461, \"rank\": 0.000555786024209706, \"text\": \"Jews\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jews\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jews\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the same systemic threat\", \"from\": 2707, \"to\": 2731}, {\"ngram\": \"hate crimes\", \"from\": 2735, \"to\": 2746}, {\"ngram\": \"Blacks\", \"from\": 2763, \"to\": 2769}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As the British say, we should \\\"Keep calm and carry on.\\\"\", \"from\": 2771, \"to\": 2826, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"calm\", \"from\": 2807, \"to\": 2811}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Liberals would also do well to watch their words and actions lest they antagonize the Catholic public.\", \"from\": 2828, \"to\": 2930, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2914, \"end\": 2922, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 0.9998984658654222, \"rank\": 0.00010151909565381063, \"text\": \"Catholic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Liberals\", \"from\": 2828, \"to\": 2836}, {\"ngram\": \"their words\", \"from\": 2865, \"to\": 2876}, {\"ngram\": \"actions\", \"from\": 2881, \"to\": 2888}]}, {\"sentence\": \"You can only poke us in the nose so many times before we hit back.\", \"from\": 2931, \"to\": 2997, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 2949, \"to\": 2951}, {\"ngram\": \"the nose\", \"from\": 2955, \"to\": 2963}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Allowing Catholic hospitals and doctors to refuse to do medical procedures that violate their consciences would be a good beginning.\", \"from\": 2999, \"to\": 3131, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3008, \"end\": 3016, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 0.9998984658654222, \"rank\": 0.00010151909565381063, \"text\": \"Catholic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"doctors\", \"from\": 3031, \"to\": 3038}, {\"ngram\": \"medical procedures\", \"from\": 3055, \"to\": 3073}, {\"ngram\": \"their consciences\", \"from\": 3087, \"to\": 3104}, {\"ngram\": \"a good beginning\", \"from\": 3114, \"to\": 3130}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Allowing a few minor exemptions to believers is a small price to pay for avoiding political controversy and having your policies generally accepted.\", \"from\": 3132, \"to\": 3280, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a few minor exemptions\", \"from\": 3141, \"to\": 3163}, {\"ngram\": \"believers\", \"from\": 3167, \"to\": 3176}, {\"ngram\": \"a small price\", \"from\": 3180, \"to\": 3193}, {\"ngram\": \"political controversy\", \"from\": 3214, \"to\": 3235}, {\"ngram\": \"your policies\", \"from\": 3247, \"to\": 3260}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was politically stupid, for example, to take on the Little Sisters of the Poor, who devote their lives to helping the sick and elderly.\", \"from\": 3281, \"to\": 3419, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"example\", \"from\": 3312, \"to\": 3319}, {\"ngram\": \"the Little Sisters\", \"from\": 3332, \"to\": 3350}, {\"ngram\": \"the Poor\", \"from\": 3354, \"to\": 3362}, {\"ngram\": \"their lives\", \"from\": 3375, \"to\": 3386}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Artists tend to push the boundaries of what is considered acceptable, such as having a crucifix at the bottom of a urinal.\", \"from\": 3421, \"to\": 3543, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Artists\", \"from\": 3421, \"to\": 3428}, {\"ngram\": \"the boundaries\", \"from\": 3442, \"to\": 3456}, {\"ngram\": \"a crucifix\", \"from\": 3506, \"to\": 3516}, {\"ngram\": \"the bottom\", \"from\": 3520, \"to\": 3530}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While such \\\"art\\\" is protected by the free speech clause of the First Amendment, Catholic citizens have a right to object when their tax dollars are used to promote such art - just as we have a right to object when our tax dollars are used for any purpose we do not like.\", \"from\": 3544, \"to\": 3814, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3624, \"end\": 3632, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 0.9998984658654222, \"rank\": 0.00010151909565381063, \"text\": \"Catholic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"such \\\"art\", \"from\": 3550, \"to\": 3559}, {\"ngram\": \"the free speech clause\", \"from\": 3577, \"to\": 3599}, {\"ngram\": \"the First Amendment\", \"from\": 3603, \"to\": 3622}, {\"ngram\": \"a right\", \"from\": 3647, \"to\": 3654}, {\"ngram\": \"their tax dollars\", \"from\": 3670, \"to\": 3687}, {\"ngram\": \"such art\", \"from\": 3708, \"to\": 3716}, {\"ngram\": \"a right\", \"from\": 3735, \"to\": 3742}, {\"ngram\": \"our tax dollars\", \"from\": 3758, \"to\": 3773}, {\"ngram\": \"any purpose\", \"from\": 3787, \"to\": 3798}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The artists who produced the opening ceremony of the Olympics, for the most part, did a marvelous job.\", \"from\": 3816, \"to\": 3918, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The artists\", \"from\": 3816, \"to\": 3827}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening ceremony\", \"from\": 3841, \"to\": 3861}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 3865, \"to\": 3877}, {\"ngram\": \"the most part\", \"from\": 3883, \"to\": 3896}, {\"ngram\": \"a marvelous job\", \"from\": 3902, \"to\": 3917}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I grimaced when the \\\"Last Supper\\\" scene appeared because that is what I saw it for, as did so many Christians.\", \"from\": 3919, \"to\": 4029, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4018, \"end\": 4028, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.613671510413598, \"rank\": 0.6295361697345307, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the \\\"Last Supper\\\" scene\", \"from\": 3935, \"to\": 3958}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Regardless, I quickly forgot about it as the show moved on to other acts.\", \"from\": 4030, \"to\": 4103, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the show\", \"from\": 4071, \"to\": 4079}, {\"ngram\": \"other acts\", \"from\": 4092, \"to\": 4102}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I would have cut the act, but I also admit it was done in the context of humorous episodes dealing with other great works of art.\", \"from\": 4104, \"to\": 4233, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the act\", \"from\": 4121, \"to\": 4128}, {\"ngram\": \"the context\", \"from\": 4162, \"to\": 4173}, {\"ngram\": \"humorous episodes\", \"from\": 4177, \"to\": 4194}, {\"ngram\": \"other great works\", \"from\": 4208, \"to\": 4225}, {\"ngram\": \"art\", \"from\": 4229, \"to\": 4232}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Also distasteful was the decapitation scene reminiscent of the Reign of Terror.\", \"from\": 4235, \"to\": 4314, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the decapitation scene\", \"from\": 4256, \"to\": 4278}, {\"ngram\": \"the Reign\", \"from\": 4294, \"to\": 4303}, {\"ngram\": \"Terror\", \"from\": 4307, \"to\": 4313}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Capital punishment is not funny.\", \"from\": 4315, \"to\": 4347, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Capital punishment\", \"from\": 4315, \"to\": 4333}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Catholic bishops objected to what they saw as a \\\"Last Supper\\\" parody.\", \"from\": 4349, \"to\": 4418, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4349, \"end\": 4357, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 0.9998984658654222, \"rank\": 0.000101